postcontent:
One of the first manual feed 22's I picked up.  My collection has upgraded since and this one needs to move along to someone who will use it.

Very nice wood for a shooter-grade vintage 22.  I did not refinish it.  It took quite a bit of scrubbing with Murphy's oil soap to remove the dirt then some orange oil.

The metal has an even smooth patina, no rust.

The bolt handle was plated at one time.

Marbles rear sight was on it when I got it.

One of the extractor screws is not original but everything functions fine.

I have shot super colibre, mini mag, CB shorts..pretty much every ammo and it feeds them all.  Quite accurate and quiet due to the long barrel.

A cool, old, very usable shooter.

No trades.  Raising money for a bolt action build.

title: For Sale/Trade:  WTB: Glock 20 (Gen 3 or 4; SF or Standard; New or Used), Will Trade my Springfield XDs .45 ACP + Extras
postcontent:
Looking for a Glock 20 (Gen 3/4; SF or Standard; New or Used).  I will trade for my Springfield Armory XDs .45 Auto (post recall) plus extras.

This SA XDs .45 is in like new condition.  I've cleaned and lubed it thoroughly after every range trip (4 total).  I bought it from Targetmaster in Chadds Ford about a year ago for $620 brand new.  It has a total of 300-400 rounds through it including about 6 different types of hollow points and has never had a hiccup either before or after the recall.  I sent it back to Springfield for about 2 months for the recall/upgrade and it was returned with everything performed which you can verify by the roll pin through the grip safety.  I also have all the paperwork for this (purchasing and recall).  I put Talon grips on it (and both of the extenders for the 2 extended 7 round mags that will be included with it) which greatly increased the control of this weapon as well as dampen the recoil.  I personally don't feel the recoil is bad at all on this gun however if you're recoil sensitive, a .45 this small probably isn't the gun for you.  If you aren't, then this is the PERFECT CCW!  This gun is +P rated however I've never fired any through it so I can't comment what the recoil is like with +P's but I'm sure you can find someone that has reviewed it with them online.  I really don't want to get rid of it but I want even more to acquire a Glock 20 and this is the only way I can afford it (not to mention I can't even find a 20 at any local gun shops).

This package includes:

-SA XDs .45 ACP, 3.3" barrel, fiber optic sights (includes extra red and yellow/greenish fiber, very easy to swap out/replace)
-2 Factory 5 round magazines
-2 Factory 7 round magazines (both have grip extensions with talon grips installed on them to mate up perfectly with the grip)
-Sheppard Leather/Kydex IWB Holster (pictured)
-Pocket Holster
-Everything that was originally included with the gun (SA Large Black Hard Plastic case (very nice), manual, lock, spent casing, PADDLE OWB HOLSTER, EXTRA MAGAZINE HOLDER, etc.)
-2 50 Round Boxes of Federal Premium Tactical 230gr HST's (Best defense rounds out there IMO, do some research, hard to find and not cheap)

I REALLY would like to do a straight trade for a Glock 20 and some cash can go either way depending on what you have and the shape it's in.  If I must sell it to get the money to go find and buy the Glock 20 I will but the price is firm as this XDs is a beautiful, perfectly kept firearm and includes the extras and ammo.

I have a .300 Weatherby Mark V Deluxe rifle for sale.  This rifle is in good condition.  It is a Japan made Weatherby and shoots sub MOA EASY.  I can shoot 3 shots under the size of a nickel using hand loads.
